ux.name: ux

revisions.description: This MIB will describe the entries for the UX line of products.

ux.description: The MIB module for net.com entities.

chasiDescUX2000.name: chasiDescUX2000
chasiDescUX2000.description: The description for the UX2000 chassis type

chasiDescUX1000.name: chasiDescUX1000
chasiDescUX1000.description: The description for the UX1000 chassis type

chasiType.name: chasiType
chasiType.description: The chassis type for the system.

uxAlarmCfgTable.name: uxAlarmCfgTable
uxAlarmCfgTable.description: This table gives the information about the alarms and events that this device is capable of generating. When a condition satisfying the alarms configured in this table occurs, an alarm is posted in uxActAlarmTable with associated information.

uxAlarmCfgEntry.name: uxAlarmCfgEntry
uxAlarmCfgEntry.description: An entry in the alarm table

uxAlarmIndex.name: uxAlarmIndex
uxAlarmIndex.description: Index of this alarm/event in the config table. This will be the combination of uxAlarmID and uxAlarmSubID uxAlarmIndex =uxAlarmID *65536+ uxAlarmSubID

uxAlarmSeverity.name: uxAlarmSeverity
uxAlarmSeverity.description: Alarm severity level. Eg: none warning minor major critical

uxAlarmCategory.name: uxAlarmCategory
uxAlarmCategory.description: Alarm/event category number. As per Bell Core Standard GR-1248-CORE

uxAlarmCancelType.name: uxAlarmCancelType
uxAlarmCancelType.description: When an alarm is configured as auto-cancel(1), it clears from the UX active alarm table, when the condition causing it goes away. These alarms do not need explicit user intervention to cancel (clear) them. Non-auto-cancel(0) alarm requires user intervention to clear from the active alarm table. User needs to cancel (clear) it explicitly by setting the corresponding column object in the active alarm table.

uxAlarmEvtType.name: uxAlarmEvtType
uxAlarmEvtType.description: Type of the evnt, whether it is an alarm or a normal event

uxAlarmDecodeKey.name: uxAlarmDecodeKey
uxAlarmDecodeKey.description: Decode key that is used to interpret alarm/event instances when the alarms are posted to active alarm Table. The index attribute uxAlarmInstanceID is decoded based on the value of this attribute. Eg: Decode Key - shelf;card;port Possible decode keys are: shelf, shelf;card, shelf;interface;card;port, service, channel, username, IPAddress, etc.. AFFECTS: uxAlarmInstanceID This attribute affects uxAlarmInstanceID as explained in the example above.

uxAlarmClrID.name: uxAlarmClrID
uxAlarmClrID.description: Clearing event Event ID of this alarm. Applicable to the alarms for which the auto clear is set

uxAlarmClrSubID.name: uxAlarmClrSubID
uxAlarmClrSubID.description: Clearing event Event sub ID of this alarm. Applicable to the alarms for which the auto clear is set.

uxAlarmDescription.name: uxAlarmDescription
uxAlarmDescription.description: Alarm description. Any info user wants to note

uxActAlarmTable.name: uxActAlarmTable
uxActAlarmTable.description: Active Alarm table in the system

uxActAlarmEntry.name: uxActAlarmEntry
uxActAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the active alarm table

uxAlarmConfigIndex.name: uxAlarmConfigIndex
uxAlarmConfigIndex.description: Index value of Alarm configuration number

uxAlarmActiveSeverity.name: uxAlarmActiveSeverity
uxAlarmActiveSeverity.description: Alarm severity level. Eg: none warning minor major critical

uxAlarmActiveCategory.name: uxAlarmActiveCategory
uxAlarmActiveCategory.description: Alarm/event category number. As per Bell Core Standard GR-1248-CORE

uxAlarmActiveCancelType.name: uxAlarmActiveCancelType
uxAlarmActiveCancelType.description: When an alarm is configured as auto-cancel(1), it clears from the UX active alarm table, when the condition causing it goes away. These alarms do not need explicit user intervention to cancel (clear) them. Non-auto-cancel(0) alarm requires user intervention to clear from the active alarm table. User needs to cancel (clear) it explicitly by setting the corresponding column object in the active alarm table.

uxAlarmActiveFirstOccur.name: uxAlarmActiveFirstOccur
uxAlarmActiveFirstOccur.description: Alarm first occurrence Time displayed in milli sec.

uxAlarmActiveLastOccur.name: uxAlarmActiveLastOccur
uxAlarmActiveLastOccur.description: Alarm last occurrence Time displayed in milli sec.

uxAlarmActiveCount.name: uxAlarmActiveCount
uxAlarmActiveCount.description: Number of times this alert occurred. This count is relevant only for non-auto-cancelling alerts.

uxAlarmActiveDecodeKey.name: uxAlarmActiveDecodeKey
uxAlarmActiveDecodeKey.description: Decode key that is used to interpret alarm/event instances when the alarms are posted to active alarm Table. The index attribute uxAlarmInstanceID is decoded based on the value of this attribute. Eg: Decode Key - shelf;card;port Possible decode keys are: shelf, shelf;card, shelf;interface;card;port, service, channel, username, IPAddress, etc.. AFFECTS: uxAlarmInstanceID This attribute affects uxAlarmInstanceID as explained in the example above.

uxAlarmActiveSourceInstance.name: uxAlarmActiveSourceInstance
uxAlarmActiveSourceInstance.description: Instance that has generated this alert. This is encoded as illustrated in the following example : decode key = shelf;card;port Source instance = 1;1;1 indicates that the alert is generated on shelf 1 card 1 and port 1 DEPENDS ON: uxAlarmDecodeKey Management station will use uxAlarmDecodeKey to decode this instance.

uxAlarmActiveState.name: uxAlarmActiveState
uxAlarmActiveState.description: Informs if an active alarm is acknowledged/unacknowledged/cancelled.

uxAlarmActiveClrEvtID.name: uxAlarmActiveClrEvtID
uxAlarmActiveClrEvtID.description: Clearing event Event ID of this alarm. Applicable to the alarms for which the auto clear is set

uxAlarmActiveClrEvtSubID.name: uxAlarmActiveClrEvtSubID
uxAlarmActiveClrEvtSubID.description: Clearing event Event sub ID of this alarm. Applicable to the alarms for which the auto clear is set.

uxAlarmActiveDescription.name: uxAlarmActiveDescription
uxAlarmActiveDescription.description: Alarm description. Any info user wants to note

uxDSPResourceTable.name: uxDSPResourceTable
uxDSPResourceTable.description: This table gives the information about the DSP resources in UX.

uxDSPResourceEntry.name: uxDSPResourceEntry
uxDSPResourceEntry.description: An entry in the DSP resource table

uxDSPIsPresent.name: uxDSPIsPresent
uxDSPIsPresent.description: If the DSP resource is present. This is because we list all the possible DSP resources through this table and this object specifies if the DSP resource is actually installed on UX.

uxDSPCPUUsage.name: uxDSPCPUUsage
uxDSPCPUUsage.description: DSP Resource usage in % rounded of to the next integer.

uxDSPChannelsInUse.name: uxDSPChannelsInUse
uxDSPChannelsInUse.description: Number of channels in use by this DSP

uxCodecsSupported.name: uxCodecsSupported
uxCodecsSupported.description: Codecs supported by this DSP, displayed as a '|' seperated string

uxDSX0ConfigEntry.name: uxDSX0ConfigEntry
uxDSX0ConfigEntry.description: An entry in the DS0 Configuration table. There is an entry in this table for each DS0 interface.

uxDSX0Lastchange.name: uxDSX0Lastchange
uxDSX0Lastchange.description: Last change of status on this DS0 in EPOCH secs

uxModuleTable.name: uxModuleTable
uxModuleTable.description: This table gives the information about all the installed Modules in UX.

uxModuleEntry.name: uxModuleEntry
uxModuleEntry.description: An entry in the Module table

uxModuleIndex.name: uxModuleIndex
uxModuleIndex.description: Index of the Module. It also represents the physical location of the card/module on the system. NOTE: For different UX Chassis, the index of modules/cards may differ.

uxModuleType.name: uxModuleType
uxModuleType.description: Module type indicating the physical module type. Integer values 7, 8, 9, 10, 15 - reserved for future modules.

uxModuleSerialNumber.name: uxModuleSerialNumber
uxModuleSerialNumber.description: Module serial number information Example: A4000110040059

uxModuleMfgWeek.name: uxModuleMfgWeek
uxModuleMfgWeek.description: Module manufacturing week number NOTE: This object is not applicable for uxModuleType of PowerSupply type. For PowerSupply Modules, 0 will be returned.

uxModuleMfgYear.name: uxModuleMfgYear
uxModuleMfgYear.description: Module manufacturing year number NOTE: This object is not applicable for uxModuleType of PowerSupply type. For PowerSupply Modules, 0 will be returned.

uxPSUTable.name: uxPSUTable
uxPSUTable.description: This table provides health and runtime information on all Power Supplies on UX. This table returns all applicable power supply slots. NOTE: THIS MIB IS NOT SUPPORTED FOR UX1000 MODEL

uxPSUEntry.name: uxPSUEntry
uxPSUEntry.description: An entry in the PSU table

uxPSUIndex.name: uxPSUIndex
uxPSUIndex.description: Index of the Power Supply. NOTE: UX2000: Index 1, is the left PSU Index 2, is the right PSU

uxPSUIsPresent.name: uxPSUIsPresent
uxPSUIsPresent.description: Provides indication if the power supply is present on the device.

uxPSUIsInputGood.name: uxPSUIsInputGood
uxPSUIsInputGood.description: Provides status of PSU Input health. This could be used to deduce the health state of the Power Supply as following: uxPSUIsPresent(1) and yes(1) - Power Supply is Up no(2) - Power Supply is Down

uxPSUInputType.name: uxPSUInputType
uxPSUInputType.description: Provides the type of PSU Input i.e. AC or DC

uxPSUPowerIn.name: uxPSUPowerIn
uxPSUPowerIn.description: Provides Power (W) coming into the supply

uxPSUPowerOut.name: uxPSUPowerOut
uxPSUPowerOut.description: Provides Power (W) going out from the supply

uxPSUVoltageIn.name: uxPSUVoltageIn
uxPSUVoltageIn.description: Provides Voltage coming into the supply

uxPSUVoltageOut.name: uxPSUVoltageOut
uxPSUVoltageOut.description: Provides Voltage going out from the supply This information is returned in 1000s of the unit value

uxPSUCurrentIn.name: uxPSUCurrentIn
uxPSUCurrentIn.description: Provides Current (A) coming into the supply This information is returned in 1000s of the unit value

uxPSUCurrentOut.name: uxPSUCurrentOut
uxPSUCurrentOut.description: Provides Current (A) going out from the supply This information is returned in 1000s of the unit value

uxPSUFanSpeed1.name: uxPSUFanSpeed1
uxPSUFanSpeed1.description: Provides speed (RPM) of the Fan 1 of the supply

uxPSUFanSpeed2.name: uxPSUFanSpeed2
uxPSUFanSpeed2.description: Provides speed (RPM) of the Fan 2 of the supply

uxFanTable.name: uxFanTable
uxFanTable.description: This table gives the information about all the installed Fans on UX. NOTE: THIS MIB IS NOT SUPPORTED FOR UX1000 MODEL

uxFanEntry.name: uxFanEntry
uxFanEntry.description: An entry in the Fan table

uxFanSpeed.name: uxFanSpeed
uxFanSpeed.description: Speed (RPM) of the Fan Note: Fan can be considered Down if the speed is 0

uxCardTable.name: uxCardTable
uxCardTable.description: This table gives information about all the installed Cards on UX. NOTE: THIS MIB IS NOT SUPPORTED FOR UX1000 MODEL

uxCardEntry.name: uxCardEntry
uxCardEntry.description: An entry in the Card table

uxCardType.name: uxCardType
uxCardType.description: Card type indicating the physical card type. Integer values 5 to 16 do not indicate a physical card type.

uxCardServiceStatus.name: uxCardServiceStatus
uxCardServiceStatus.description: Operational status of the installed card. Note: This attribute is not applicable for cards/modules on UX1000 hardware.

uxSystemHighestSeverityAlarm.name: uxSystemHighestSeverityAlarm
uxSystemHighestSeverityAlarm.description: Provides highest severity of all active alarms in the system.

uxSystemCurrentCPUUsage.name: uxSystemCurrentCPUUsage
uxSystemCurrentCPUUsage.description: Provides CPU Usage statistics for the current interval.

uxSystemCurrentMemoryUsage.name: uxSystemCurrentMemoryUsage
uxSystemCurrentMemoryUsage.description: Provides Memory Usage statistics for the current interval.

uxLicenseCurrentPeakSIPCall.name: uxLicenseCurrentPeakSIPCall
uxLicenseCurrentPeakSIPCall.description: Peak value of used SIP call licenses for the current 1 hour interval.

uxLicenseCurrentPeakSIPRegistration.name: uxLicenseCurrentPeakSIPRegistration
uxLicenseCurrentPeakSIPRegistration.description: Peak value of used SIP Registrations licenses for the current interval.

uxDSPPeakCurrentUsage.name: uxDSPPeakCurrentUsage
uxDSPPeakCurrentUsage.description: Peak DSP usage for the current 1 hour interval.

uxLicenseCurrentPeakTDMChannel.name: uxLicenseCurrentPeakTDMChannel
uxLicenseCurrentPeakTDMChannel.description: Peak value of used TDM channel licenses.

uxLicenseCurrentPeakDSP.name: uxLicenseCurrentPeakDSP
uxLicenseCurrentPeakDSP.description: Peak value of used DSP licenses.

uxSystemUsageStatsIntervalTable.name: uxSystemUsageStatsIntervalTable
uxSystemUsageStatsIntervalTable.description: The System Usage Interval table contains various system usage statitics collected over the previous 4 hours.The past 4 hours are broken into 240 completed 1 minute intervals. Each row in this table represents one such interval .

uxSystemUsageIntervalEntry.name: uxSystemUsageIntervalEntry
uxSystemUsageIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the System Usage Interval table

uxSystemUsageIntervalNumber.name: uxSystemUsageIntervalNumber
uxSystemUsageIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 240, where 1 is the most recently completed 1 minute interval and 240 is the 1 minute interval completed 239 minutes prior to interval 1.

uxSystemUsageIntervalCPUUsage.name: uxSystemUsageIntervalCPUUsage
uxSystemUsageIntervalCPUUsage.description: CPU Usage statistics for 1 minute interval.

uxSystemUsageIntervalMemoryUsage.name: uxSystemUsageIntervalMemoryUsage
uxSystemUsageIntervalMemoryUsage.description: Memory Usage statistics for 1 minute interval.

uxDSPPeakUsageStatsIntervalTable.name: uxDSPPeakUsageStatsIntervalTable
uxDSPPeakUsageStatsIntervalTable.description: The DSP Usage Stats table contains various statistics being collected by DSP for the previous 24 hours. The past 24 hours are broken into 24 completed 1 hour intervals. Each row in this table represents one such interval.

uxDSPPeakUsageIntervalEntry.name: uxDSPPeakUsageIntervalEntry
uxDSPPeakUsageIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the System Usage Current table

uxDSPPeakUsageIntervalIndex.name: uxDSPPeakUsageIntervalIndex
uxDSPPeakUsageIntervalIndex.description: The Index value which identifies the interval.

uxUserStatsPeakSessionsCurrentInerval.name: uxUserStatsPeakSessionsCurrentInerval
uxUserStatsPeakSessionsCurrentInerval.description: Provides peak number of user sessions in the current interval.

uxUserStatsIntervalTable.name: uxUserStatsIntervalTable
uxUserStatsIntervalTable.description: Provides peak number of user sessions for the specified interval.

uxUserStatsIntervalEntry.name: uxUserStatsIntervalEntry
uxUserStatsIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the user statistics interval table.

uxUserStatsIntervalNumber.name: uxUserStatsIntervalNumber
uxUserStatsIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 24, where 1 is the most recently completed 1 hour interval and 24 is the 1 hour interval completed 23 hours and 45 minutes prior to interval 1.

uxUserStatsPeakSessions.name: uxUserStatsPeakSessions
uxUserStatsPeakSessions.description: Peak user sessions during the requested interval.
